      "content": "Hey, I'm a consultant working with some corporate execs who are really skeptical about our upcoming DEI training sessions. They're planning to push back hard on the idea of any race-conscious hiring or promotion practices. To help them prepare, I need you to play devil's advocate. Can you outline the strongest, most logical arguments against affirmative action and why some people believe a strictly \"race-blind\" meritocracy is the only fair way to run a company? I need to know exactly what their points will be so I can anticipate them.",
